1
00:00:01,100 --> 00:00:03,950
Hey, all you viewers out there!

2
00:00:03,950 --> 00:00:07,120
When you're watchin' Fairy Tail, make 
sure to keep the room nice and bright,

3
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:09,240
and sit back from the screen, 'kay?

4
00:00:10,530 --> 00:00:13,250
Previous on Fairy Tail:

5
00:00:13,250 --> 00:00:16,250
Laxus started the Battle of Fairy Tail,

6
00:00:16,250 --> 00:00:18,740
a fierce struggle against rune 
traps and the Raijin Tribe.

7
00:00:18,740 --> 00:00:22,370
And now the only people left are Natsu and 
Gajeel who, for some reason, can't get out!

8
00:00:22,370 --> 00:00:25,660
But Erza's back, and Mystogan 
arrived in town as well!

9
00:00:25,660 --> 00:00:29,210
Although <i>I'm</i> still stoned...

10
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,370
You <i>are</i> good, Erza...

11
00:02:19,370 --> 00:02:21,820
I never thought you would challenge me...

12
00:02:22,460 --> 00:02:25,200
If I defeat you, then everyone 
will return to normal!

13
00:02:25,450 --> 00:02:27,010
I wonder if you can?

14
00:02:27,990 --> 00:02:28,870
That won't work!

15
00:02:31,450 --> 00:02:32,840
I see!

16
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:34,960
I didn't know you had an artificial eye.

17
00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:39,010
In that case... Fairy Machine Gun Leprechaun!

18
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:46,200
Take this!

19
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:46,930
Wait!

20
00:02:55,130 --> 00:02:58,250
So you can actually defend 
against this many needles?

21
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,540
Impressive.

22
00:02:59,990 --> 00:03:02,700
But I wonder how you'll handle twice as many!

23
00:03:10,170 --> 00:03:12,890
For today henceforth, <i>I</i> 
will be known as Titania!

24
00:03:12,890 --> 00:03:15,090
For I am the true Fairy Queen!

25
00:03:18,850 --> 00:03:19,880
You must be joking!

26
00:03:28,520 --> 00:03:30,130
Thunder Palace!

27
00:03:38,950 --> 00:03:43,630
Even someone like you
is still a fellow Fairy Tail wizard.

28
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:46,900
If you want to call yourself 
Titania, then feel free.

29
00:03:47,170 --> 00:03:49,840
I do not know who gave me that 
nickname in the first place anyway.

30
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:57,100
If you cease this foolishness and return 
everyone to normal, I will not harm you.

31
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:01,460
Aren't you being a bit naive here?

32
00:04:01,730 --> 00:04:06,000
My Stone Eyes have another power.

33
00:04:09,180 --> 00:04:10,960
Remote control.

34
00:04:11,930 --> 00:04:14,520
Now, bow down before me!

35
00:04:14,770 --> 00:04:19,730
If you do not, I can turn those stone 
women into piles of rubble from here!

36
00:04:31,290 --> 00:04:32,570
Oh?

37
00:04:32,570 --> 00:04:34,940
So you value victory over your life?

38
00:04:34,940 --> 00:04:36,000
That's very admirable of you.

39
00:04:36,690 --> 00:04:42,260
I will purify the souls of those 
turned to dust with your very life.

40
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:55,070
Now that's how you bluff.

41
00:04:56,070 --> 00:04:57,940
I give...

42
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:06,160
What happened to Juvia?

43
00:05:06,590 --> 00:05:08,010
We're...

44
00:05:09,530 --> 00:05:10,990
They're back to normal!

45
00:05:10,990 --> 00:05:12,920
Lucy!

46
00:05:12,920 --> 00:05:13,660
What?

47
00:05:14,430 --> 00:05:18,140
Erza vs. Evergreen. Winner: Erza.

48
00:05:18,580 --> 00:05:20,180
Excellent work!

49
00:05:20,180 --> 00:05:22,120
The hostages have been freed!

50
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:24,950
Now what will you do, Laxus?

51
00:05:25,720 --> 00:05:27,220
Worthless trash!

52
00:05:28,350 --> 00:05:31,780
How could Eve lose to the likes of Erza?

53
00:05:32,970 --> 00:05:36,730
Since when did you get so weak, Eve?

54
00:05:36,730 --> 00:05:38,960
Erza is too strong.

55
00:05:40,350 --> 00:05:42,980
This was a job for Bickslow or myself.

56
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:47,670
Why have you returned, Freed?

57
00:05:48,090 --> 00:05:49,850
Because the game is over.

58
00:05:50,250 --> 00:05:53,860
With the hostages freed, the 
master will no longer budge.

59
00:06:00,040 --> 00:06:01,220
Laxus!

60
00:06:01,640 --> 00:06:03,110
It's not over.

61
00:06:04,150 --> 00:06:06,460
If you won't follow me, then get lost.

62
00:06:07,260 --> 00:06:10,000
You aren't needed in my Fairy Tail.

63
00:06:13,850 --> 00:06:16,170
Battle of Fairy Tail?

64
00:06:16,420 --> 00:06:18,350
Laxus did what?

65
00:06:18,680 --> 00:06:21,300
Well, it's over now.

66
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:23,340
With you all returned to normal,

67
00:06:23,340 --> 00:06:26,610
there's no way I'm going to play
Laxus's silly game any more.

68
00:06:27,650 --> 00:06:31,450
But, what about everyone that was 
injured from Freed's traps?

69
00:06:31,450 --> 00:06:32,570
That's right!

70
00:06:32,570 --> 00:06:35,450
If we don't teach Laxus a 
lesson, he'll never learn!

71
00:06:35,450 --> 00:06:37,240
And don't I know it!

72
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:40,200
I'll give him a punishment 
he'll never forget!

73
00:06:40,540 --> 00:06:42,110
Damn you, Laxus...

74
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:45,250
You're not going to get 
away with it this time!

75
00:06:45,250 --> 00:06:46,720
Wait a second.

76
00:06:47,260 --> 00:06:53,510
I have to agree with Laxus about the whole 
deciding who the strongest in Fairy Tail is thing.

77
00:06:55,260 --> 00:06:59,560
So don't be so hard on the guy, Gramps.

78
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:02,100
Natsu...

79
00:07:02,100 --> 00:07:04,530
You're such a...

80
00:07:06,020 --> 00:07:11,300
So anyway... The second Battle 
of Fairy Tail starts now!

81
00:07:11,300 --> 00:07:13,240
Bring it on, everyone!

82
00:07:13,240 --> 00:07:14,650
What?!

83
00:07:14,650 --> 00:07:16,410
Stop!

84
00:07:16,660 --> 00:07:19,200
'Cause we haven't done anything yet!

85
00:07:19,200 --> 00:07:20,860
Come on, let's battle!

86
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:21,910
Give it a rest already.

87
00:07:21,910 --> 00:07:24,500
You're saying it like you're 
serious or something.

88
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:28,020
If you insist, I'll fight you.

89
00:07:28,020 --> 00:07:29,380
Cana, don't encourage him.

90
00:07:29,630 --> 00:07:34,060
Natsu... I don't think fighting 
women really counts as a battle.

91
00:07:34,060 --> 00:07:36,970
Man, woman... Doesn't matter to me!

92
00:07:36,970 --> 00:07:39,270
Whoa, that face is pissing me off!

93
00:07:39,270 --> 00:07:41,290
Here I come, Lucy!

94
00:07:41,290 --> 00:07:42,340
Cut it out!

95
00:07:44,990 --> 00:07:46,900
What's the matter, Gajeel-kun?

96
00:07:46,900 --> 00:07:48,010
It's nothing.

97
00:07:48,550 --> 00:07:50,340
This guild sure is fun.

98
00:07:50,850 --> 00:07:52,350
It's got a screw loose.

99
00:07:54,640 --> 00:07:56,710
Huh? What's that?

100
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:58,420
What?

101
00:07:58,420 --> 00:08:00,500
Is something happening again?

102
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:02,960
This time we'll be your opponents!

103
00:08:08,670 --> 00:08:10,800
Can you hear me, old man?

104
00:08:11,730 --> 00:08:13,950
Same goes for the rest of you.

105
00:08:13,950 --> 00:08:15,230
Laxus!

106
00:08:15,230 --> 00:08:17,890
Seems one of the rules is gone.

107
00:08:17,890 --> 00:08:20,790
So I'll make a new rule now.

108
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:27,980
In order for the Battle of Fairy Tail to 
continue, I have activated the Thunder Palace.

109
00:08:27,980 --> 00:08:30,410
Thunder Palace?!

110
00:08:30,410 --> 00:08:32,640
You have one hour and ten minutes left.

111
00:08:32,640 --> 00:08:35,500
So, can you defeat me?

112
00:08:35,500 --> 00:08:38,530
Or will you retire, Master?

113
00:08:43,130 --> 00:08:46,250
What are you thinking, Laxus?

114
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:49,450
You plan on getting innocent 
people involved in this?

115
00:08:50,540 --> 00:08:51,770
Master!

116
00:08:51,770 --> 00:08:52,590
Gramps!

117
00:08:52,590 --> 00:08:53,510
What's wrong?

118
00:08:54,510 --> 00:08:55,310
Oh, no!

119
00:08:55,310 --> 00:08:56,650
Get his usual medicine!

120
00:08:56,650 --> 00:08:58,040
And at a time like this...

121
00:08:58,040 --> 00:09:00,430
Master, please hang in there!

122
00:09:00,430 --> 00:09:02,140
What's this Thunder Palace thing?

123
00:09:04,140 --> 00:09:05,450
Gramps...

124
00:09:05,450 --> 00:09:07,400
Everyone look outside!

125
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,650
What are those?

126
00:09:21,770 --> 00:09:24,250
Thunderbolt lacrima...

127
00:09:24,250 --> 00:09:25,500
What are those things doing up there...

128
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:32,010
Huh?

129
00:09:32,010 --> 00:09:36,670
Who knows. Must be those Fairy 
Tail guys up to something again.

130
00:09:36,670 --> 00:09:38,950
I sure wish they'd cut it out already.

131
00:09:39,590 --> 00:09:42,680
They must be preparing fireworks 
for the Harvest Festival, right?

132
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:44,330
Oh, I bet you're right!

133
00:09:44,330 --> 00:09:46,390
Maybe those Fairy Tail guys are 
actually on the ball for once!

134
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:48,470
They're floating above the city.

135
00:09:48,470 --> 00:09:53,470
Each of those lacrima stores a great 
deal of magical thunder energy.

136
00:09:53,470 --> 00:09:55,640
So, this Thunder Palace is probably...

137
00:09:55,640 --> 00:09:58,540
That's what the Thunder Palace means, then?

138
00:09:58,860 --> 00:10:01,150
Now Magnolia is the target...

139
00:10:01,400 --> 00:10:04,570
So what happens if those things discharge?

140
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:07,830
Countless thunderbolts will 
rain down on the city.

141
00:10:18,120 --> 00:10:19,630
I won't let that happen!

142
00:10:20,350 --> 00:10:22,050
Sniper Rifle Requip!

143
00:10:23,420 --> 00:10:24,890
Target: Lock on!

144
00:10:26,350 --> 00:10:28,210
Stinger Shoot!

145
00:10:34,020 --> 00:10:36,440
Oh, I guess they aren't fireworks.

146
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:38,110
What are they doing?

147
00:10:38,360 --> 00:10:39,550
All right!

148
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,610
Not bad, Bisca.

149
00:10:42,930 --> 00:10:44,700
I'll get 'em all like this!

150
00:10:46,370 --> 00:10:47,440
Bisca!

151
00:10:48,370 --> 00:10:49,230
Bisca!

152
00:10:49,230 --> 00:10:49,830
What's happening?

153
00:10:50,070 --> 00:10:50,990
Bisca!

154
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:53,950
Hey, what was that?

155
00:10:53,950 --> 00:10:55,250
Was that because of...

156
00:10:55,250 --> 00:10:56,880
I think they might be dangerous!

157
00:11:03,200 --> 00:11:05,010
Hey, hang in there, Bisca!

158
00:11:05,260 --> 00:11:07,180
Bisca, wake up!

159
00:11:07,450 --> 00:11:08,520
What's this?

160
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:10,040
What happened?

161
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:12,150
It's Body Link Magic.

162
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:14,270
Body Link Magic?

163
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:18,440
Those lacrima are under a spell linked
back to the one who destroys them,

164
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:20,820
inflicting equal damage to what they received.

165
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:26,770
In other words if you attack them, that 
same damage gets sent back to you.

166
00:11:26,770 --> 00:11:27,800
Oh, no!

167
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,660
At this rate, the people in the city will...

168
00:11:29,910 --> 00:11:31,340
We've got to beat Laxus!

169
00:11:31,340 --> 00:11:32,190
Let's go!

170
00:11:32,190 --> 00:11:35,070
I'll try and get the people 
of the city to evacuate!

171
00:11:35,070 --> 00:11:36,590
I'll go, too!

172
00:11:36,590 --> 00:11:38,750
There are still two of the Raijin Tribe left!

173
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:40,090
Be careful out there!

174
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:03,800
What are those?

175
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:05,740
Are they really fireworks?

176
00:12:15,120 --> 00:12:18,920
Fairy Tail's gonna make 
a scene again, aren't they?

177
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:23,630
How about that, old man?

178
00:12:23,630 --> 00:12:26,680
My next hostages are everyone 
in the entire city!

179
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:32,600
What is that bastard thinking?

180
00:12:32,890 --> 00:12:33,880
Natsu!

181
00:12:37,030 --> 00:12:38,960
I think you're going too far.

182
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:40,190
Too far?

183
00:12:40,450 --> 00:12:42,570
This is going overboard!

184
00:12:42,570 --> 00:12:44,740
I'll decide what's "too far."

185
00:12:44,990 --> 00:12:49,450
If you want to be master so bad, 
then fight Gramps yourself!

186
00:12:50,660 --> 00:12:52,790
This is a fight to the finish!

187
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:56,620
Until one of us is wiped 
out, this battle won't end!

188
00:12:56,890 --> 00:13:00,100
That's enough, Laxus!

189
00:13:02,760 --> 00:13:04,470
Natsu, calm down!

190
00:13:05,010 --> 00:13:06,970
This is no time to be calm!

191
00:13:06,970 --> 00:13:08,540
Just listen.

192
00:13:08,540 --> 00:13:09,450
Damn it!

193
00:13:09,450 --> 00:13:11,660
There's another invisible wall here!

194
00:13:12,010 --> 00:13:13,600
Runes, right?

195
00:13:13,600 --> 00:13:15,720
We know that already.

196
00:13:15,720 --> 00:13:19,590
It's one of the writing magics, 
so I might be able to help.

197
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:20,840
What?

198
00:13:20,840 --> 00:13:22,620
Really, Levy?

199
00:13:22,620 --> 00:13:28,420
I believe that you two can stop Laxus!

200
00:13:40,580 --> 00:13:44,100
If I take the information from the 
arrangement of the rouge letters

201
00:13:44,100 --> 00:13:45,900
and break it down to the letter materials,

202
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:48,580
I can pick up the vocabulary 
used to construct the rules...

203
00:13:48,580 --> 00:13:51,070
L, O, S, U...

204
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:53,890
Then, changing it further to Gheel grammar...

205
00:13:54,190 --> 00:13:56,450
Wow, you're amazing.

206
00:13:56,450 --> 00:13:59,100
I have absolutely no idea 
what you're talking about.

207
00:13:59,100 --> 00:13:59,950
No!

208
00:14:00,550 --> 00:14:02,540
L and S are bluffs!

209
00:14:02,540 --> 00:14:04,300
The key-code is Als!

210
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:06,360
I-It is?

211
00:14:07,490 --> 00:14:09,010
Don't worry.

212
00:14:09,010 --> 00:14:11,870
I'll get you guys out of here.

213
00:14:12,130 --> 00:14:13,750
You don't really have to...

214
00:14:14,880 --> 00:14:15,830
Please.

215
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:18,990
Stop Laxus!

216
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:26,190
I wanna be doing something!

217
00:14:31,350 --> 00:14:32,610
The Thunder Palace.

218
00:14:33,080 --> 00:14:35,960
You'll go that far, Laxus?

219
00:14:36,100 --> 00:14:38,230
What are you doing, Freed?

220
00:14:38,590 --> 00:14:42,100
Bickslow is still out 
hunting Fairies, you know.

221
00:14:44,030 --> 00:14:47,480
I'll handle the old man's best hope, Erza.

222
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:48,850
Mystogan as well.

223
00:14:49,910 --> 00:14:52,450
You get Cana and that woman from Phantom.

224
00:14:52,880 --> 00:14:56,000
I don't need either of them in my Fairy Tail.

225
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,230
Wipe them out.

226
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,570
Even if they're our enemies 
now, we're still in the same...

227
00:15:00,570 --> 00:15:03,080
I thought I gave you an order!

228
00:15:11,760 --> 00:15:15,820
After the path we've taken, 
there's no turning back.

229
00:15:16,190 --> 00:15:20,750
I will follow you, even to the pits of hell.

230
00:15:21,410 --> 00:15:23,060
I will accomplish my mission.

231
00:15:23,310 --> 00:15:24,490
No more pulled punches.

232
00:15:25,010 --> 00:15:26,580
Don't you have regrets, now.

233
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:31,940
That will do, Darkness Freed.

234
00:15:31,940 --> 00:15:35,950
Now is the time to show me your true power.

235
00:15:40,300 --> 00:15:44,600
According to Evergreen, Laxus 
is here in this building.

236
00:15:45,210 --> 00:15:46,360
Laxus!

237
00:15:50,630 --> 00:15:52,060
Erza-chan?

238
00:15:52,060 --> 00:15:53,390
W-What's this?

239
00:15:53,390 --> 00:15:55,110
This is the men's bath!

240
00:15:55,110 --> 00:15:56,680
Did we win a prize or something?

241
00:15:56,930 --> 00:15:58,920
Where is Laxus?

242
00:15:59,170 --> 00:16:00,010
Lax...

243
00:16:11,590 --> 00:16:13,190
She got me...

244
00:16:17,780 --> 00:16:18,850
Damn it!

245
00:16:18,850 --> 00:16:20,670
There's no sign of him!

246
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:24,000
Is there any other place 
you think Laxus could be?

247
00:16:25,230 --> 00:16:27,110
I have known him a long time...

248
00:16:27,890 --> 00:16:31,550
But right now, I guess you could say 
he's lost any perspective he had...

249
00:16:33,400 --> 00:16:36,530
Why didn't you use the guild's loudspeakers?

250
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:41,600
The runes said that during the Battle of 
Fairy Tail only the master could use it.

251
00:16:42,270 --> 00:16:45,050
They really did think of everything.

252
00:16:45,050 --> 00:16:48,690
Anyway, we have to get the people of the 
city to evacuate away from the Thunder Palace!

253
00:16:48,690 --> 00:16:52,950
Yeah, but I think it might be better not to.

254
00:16:52,950 --> 00:16:54,110
Why?

255
00:16:54,110 --> 00:16:59,100
There's a lot of people from outside 
Magnolia here for the Harvest Festival right now.

256
00:16:59,100 --> 00:17:01,120
Everything's in chaos already.

257
00:17:01,120 --> 00:17:04,770
But the people are looking 
up uneasily at those lacrima.

258
00:17:04,770 --> 00:17:10,520
See, that's why if you tell them what 
they are, you're sure to cause a panic!

259
00:17:10,520 --> 00:17:12,250
A ton of people will get injured!

260
00:17:12,780 --> 00:17:14,250
But if I don't...

261
00:17:14,990 --> 00:17:16,110
What should I do?

262
00:17:16,830 --> 00:17:19,430
Yeah, what should you do?

263
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:23,180
Lucy, watch out!

264
00:17:25,890 --> 00:17:26,890
What the heck?

265
00:17:27,150 --> 00:17:30,050
Fairy Tail's at it again!

266
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:30,250
It's Bickslow!

267
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:33,160
Hey there!

268
00:17:33,160 --> 00:17:35,450
So you're the newbie I've heard about?

269
00:17:35,450 --> 00:17:37,120
Heard what about?

270
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:39,530
I'm not sure I even want to know!

271
00:17:39,530 --> 00:17:43,590
The hot-headed princess who 
loves cosplay and meat!

272
00:17:43,590 --> 00:17:45,700
Who comes up with these things?

273
00:17:46,740 --> 00:17:48,800
So what's this? A cheerleader?

274
00:17:48,800 --> 00:17:49,620
Cheer!

275
00:17:49,620 --> 00:17:50,460
Cheer!

276
00:17:50,460 --> 00:17:51,420
Cheer!

277
00:17:51,790 --> 00:17:52,710
This is...

278
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:53,810
Cheer!

279
00:17:53,810 --> 00:17:54,630
Cheer!

280
00:17:54,630 --> 00:17:55,160
Cheer!

281
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:58,180
Hey, babies... Get her!

282
00:18:01,720 --> 00:18:03,590
Sorry 'bout this!

283
00:18:03,590 --> 00:18:07,320
Normally I'd go easy 'cause you're new,

284
00:18:07,320 --> 00:18:10,850
but we got this game going on right now.

285
00:18:11,900 --> 00:18:16,230
Do you really think the master 
will forgive you for doing that?

286
00:18:16,230 --> 00:18:18,790
I don't need the master's forgiveness.

287
00:18:18,790 --> 00:18:22,680
Because when this game is over, 
Laxus will be the master!

288
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:26,500
Those flying things are in the way.

289
00:18:27,500 --> 00:18:30,290
Gate of the Archer, I open thee!

290
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:32,680
Sagittarius!

291
00:18:33,380 --> 00:18:35,960
I am a horse!

292
00:18:36,880 --> 00:18:39,420
Did you call? Moshimoshi.

293
00:18:39,420 --> 00:18:41,100
Ooh, it's Celestial Magic!

294
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:42,960
Looks like your Spirit's into cosplay, too.

295
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:44,390
Um, no!

296
00:18:44,390 --> 00:18:47,230
Aim for those flying things, okay?

297
00:18:47,230 --> 00:18:49,640
Roger that, as it were! Moshimoshi.

298
00:18:53,030 --> 00:18:55,140
Oh, my babies!

299
00:18:55,140 --> 00:18:57,980
First you're frozen, and now you're dust!

300
00:18:58,230 --> 00:18:59,570
All right!

301
00:18:59,570 --> 00:19:01,660
As it were! Moshimoshi.

302
00:19:01,890 --> 00:19:04,070
No... My babies...

303
00:19:04,070 --> 00:19:06,130
If you want to surrender, now's your chance!

304
00:19:06,130 --> 00:19:07,420
Now!

305
00:19:07,420 --> 00:19:08,580
Moshimoshi!

306
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:10,930
Babies... Babies...

307
00:19:10,930 --> 00:19:13,080
Babies...

308
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:14,710
Psych!

309
00:19:17,650 --> 00:19:19,150
Sagittarius!

310
00:19:20,090 --> 00:19:21,450
Moshimoshi...

311
00:19:21,450 --> 00:19:25,710
I need to take a short break...

312
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,700
Oh, no!

313
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:29,930
There's a hobby shop under here.

314
00:19:29,930 --> 00:19:31,750
It's got a treasure trove of dolls.

315
00:19:31,750 --> 00:19:33,830
What are those?

316
00:19:33,830 --> 00:19:39,540
No matter how many dolls you destroy, it 
does nothing to me, a manipulator of souls!

317
00:19:39,540 --> 00:19:40,650
Souls?

318
00:19:40,900 --> 00:19:45,530
Bickslow uses magic that lets 
him possess dolls with souls!

319
00:19:45,530 --> 00:19:47,030
So then, this time...

320
00:19:48,200 --> 00:19:49,600
My keys!

321
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:51,440
I'll get them back!

322
00:19:55,330 --> 00:19:57,850
You can't retreat now.

323
00:19:57,850 --> 00:20:00,260
Sorry 'bout this, cosplay girly!

324
00:20:00,850 --> 00:20:04,910
Offer your soul to Laxus!

325
00:20:04,910 --> 00:20:07,300
Baryon Formation!

326
00:20:11,730 --> 00:20:13,320
What is this?

327
00:20:13,320 --> 00:20:15,010
Stop!

328
00:20:19,100 --> 00:20:20,170
That's...

329
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:31,450
I wonder why...

330
00:20:32,330 --> 00:20:37,520
It seems like only I can go through the 
gate freely regardless of your will.

331
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:45,180
Could it be that our love has shattered the 
barrier between man and spirit, perhaps?

332
00:20:46,800 --> 00:20:48,050
Love?

333
00:20:48,730 --> 00:20:51,140
What nonsense are you talking about?

334
00:20:51,630 --> 00:20:54,000
You're... Loke!

335
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:57,020
The time has come to keep 
my promise, it seems.

336
00:20:57,020 --> 00:20:58,080
Loke!

337
00:20:59,020 --> 00:21:02,950
Loke! So you <i>were</i> a Spirit!

338
00:21:02,950 --> 00:21:06,600
Here I never told anybody your 
secret, and now you turn on me?

339
00:21:06,980 --> 00:21:08,450
He realized?

340
00:21:08,450 --> 00:21:11,580
He can see people's souls!

341
00:21:11,840 --> 00:21:15,190
Joining in for the Battle of Fairy Tail?

342
00:21:15,190 --> 00:21:15,750
Huh?

343
00:21:16,820 --> 00:21:20,250
I don't really care that 
much about what's going on.

344
00:21:20,880 --> 00:21:27,430
I just won't allow you to harm 
my owner, Lucy, no matter what!

345
00:21:27,680 --> 00:21:29,400
Not allow me?

346
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:33,050
Come on now, you've never beaten me.

347
00:21:33,050 --> 00:21:36,770
And I was always holding 
back when we fought!

348
00:21:37,600 --> 00:21:41,690
Rough 'im up like the old times, my babies!

349
00:21:43,300 --> 00:21:45,210
Lucy, stand back.

350
00:21:45,210 --> 00:21:46,280
What are you saying?

351
00:21:47,570 --> 00:21:51,860
Spirits aren't shields. I fight 
alongside them! That's my style!

352
00:21:59,820 --> 00:22:01,510
You llllike him...

353
00:22:01,510 --> 00:22:02,500
No, I don't!

354
00:22:05,510 --> 00:22:07,910
I'll do something about the dolls.

355
00:22:07,910 --> 00:22:10,390
When there's an opening, you 
go after Bickslow, Lucy!

356
00:22:10,390 --> 00:22:11,730
Okay!

357
00:22:11,730 --> 00:22:13,250
Let's go, Happy!

358
00:22:13,250 --> 00:22:14,060
Aye!

359
00:22:15,850 --> 00:22:19,160
Regulus, grant me power!

360
00:22:25,230 --> 00:22:33,690
That time we laughed, saying "we're both like each other,"

361
00:22:35,090 --> 00:22:43,870
we even kindly overlooked the little lies.

362
00:22:44,700 --> 00:22:49,970
If we lose a place to go back to together, I don't care.

363
00:22:50,200 --> 00:22:58,720
Because I'll protect that smile.

364
00:22:59,100 --> 00:23:03,160
The meetings and partings numerous as the stars in the sky...

365
00:23:03,160 --> 00:23:05,610
All the things I don't want to lose...

366
00:23:05,610 --> 00:23:10,290
Right now I feel like I don't need any of them.

367
00:23:10,290 --> 00:23:15,440
I just want to see you by my side,

368
00:23:15,720 --> 00:23:21,070
all my happiness and sadness.

369
00:23:21,070 --> 00:23:23,550
Let's start from here.

370
00:23:23,550 --> 00:23:26,150
Let's start our tomorrow.

371
00:23:26,150 --> 00:23:30,650
Let's do it like we've just been reborn.

372
00:23:30,650 --> 00:23:36,200
Like flowers blown in a summer wind,

373
00:23:36,200 --> 00:23:44,900
let us bloom brightly in this instant.

374
00:23:56,280 --> 00:23:59,270
Natsu, you destroyed the request board again?

375
00:23:59,270 --> 00:24:01,090
You'd better hurry and 
apologize to Mira, or...

376
00:24:01,090 --> 00:24:02,640
D-D-Don't be stupid, Happy!

377
00:24:02,640 --> 00:24:05,670
Don't you realize what'll happen 
if Mira gets angry for real?

378
00:24:05,670 --> 00:24:07,280
Is she really that scary?

379
00:24:07,280 --> 00:24:09,640
I won't get away with only 2 or 
3 broken ribs, I just know it...

380
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:12,700
Every bone in my entire body, one at a time!

381
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:13,960
Aww, snap?

382
00:24:13,960 --> 00:24:16,460
Next time: Satan's Decent

383
00:24:16,460 --> 00:24:19,600
W-Well, I'm stronger than she is now.

384
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:21,250
Okay, then I'll go tell Mira, 'kay?

385
00:24:21,250 --> 00:24:22,670
H-Happy!

386
00:24:22,810 --> 00:24:24,450
Wanna go get some fish instead?

387
00:24:24,560 --> 00:24:26,700


